      "content": "I understand that you're concerned about the inconvenience of carrying an inhaler, but the whistling sound could indeed be a sign of asthma, which is known as wheezing. This sound, combined with the tightness you're feeling, suggests that your airways may be narrowed. I recommend you take the Zyrtec to alleviate the hay fever symptoms, but also give your inhaler a try to see if it helps with the wheezing. If you don't have an inhaler, you can purchase one now; it's easier to carry and use than you might think. In the meantime, keep an eye on your symptoms, and if they don't improve, or if they worsen, seek medical attention immediately. Asthma can be managed, but it's better to address it early on.",
